        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 15 at 6:07PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 607 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hot Springs, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs, Buffalo Gap, Wind Cave National Park, Cottonwood Springs
Dam, Maverick Junction, Cold Brook Reservoir, Buffalo Corrals,
northwestern Angostura Reservoir, and southeastern Custer State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
